class Solution {
public:
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        int openNeeded = 0, closeNeeded = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == '(') {
                if (closeNeeded % 2) {
                    closeNeeded++;
                    openNeeded++;
                }
                closeNeeded += 2;
            } else {
                closeNeeded--;
                if (closeNeeded < 0) {
                    openNeeded++;
                    closeNeeded += 2;
                }
            }
        }
        return openNeeded + closeNeeded;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single left-to-right pass tracks unmatched open and close requirements. When '(' appears, it needs two ')', so we add 2 to closeNeeded. If we have an odd closeNeeded, we first fix it with one extra ')' and one '('. When ')' appears, we decrement closeNeeded; if it goes negative, we add one '(' and reset closeNeeded to 1. Final answer is the sum of remaining openNeeded and closeNeeded.

